==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brunt
<hw>Brunt</hw> <pr>(br⟦ucr⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>brunt</ets>, <ets>bront</ets>, fr. Icel. <ets>bruna</ets> to rush;
cf. Icel. <ets>brenna</ets> to burn. Cf. <er>Burn</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The heat, or utmost violence, of an
onset; the strength or greatest fury of any contention; <as>as, the
<ex>brunt</ex> of a battle</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The force of a blow; shock; collision.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧And heavy <xex>brunt</xex> of cannon ball.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Hudibras.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is instantly and irrecoverably scattered by our first
<qex>brunt</qex> with some real affair of common life.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brush</ent>⟦br⟧
